tions intensifies harms associated with both treatment and punishment, especially given that the distinctions between the two have become blurred. By focusing on the stories of people whose pain and pharmaceutical treatment leads to incarceration, Smirnova challenges the binary of individual and social problems, effectively exploring how the conceptualization, diagnoses, and treatment of substance use may exacerbate outcomes such as relapse, recidivism, poverty, abuse, and death.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aDiscrimination in criminal justice administrationzUnited States. 0aDiscrimination in law enforcementzUnited States. 0aDrug abusexGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aMedication abusexSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aOpioid abusexSocial aspectszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478024330?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478024330423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478024330/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles